# EmailJS — get these from https://dashboard.emailjs.com
#
# 1. Create a free account at emailjs.com
# 2. Add an Email Service (Gmail, Outlook, etc.)  → copy the Service ID
# 3. Create an Email Template with these variables:
#      {{booking_ref}}     — e.g. QR-M8K2X9
#      {{pickup}}          — pickup location
#      {{destination}}     — drop-off location
#      {{date}}            — selected date
#      {{time}}            — selected time
#      {{passengers}}      — number of passengers
#      {{extras}}          — comma-separated extras or "None"
#      {{customer_email}}  — customer's email address
#      {{distance}}        — calculated route distance
#    Copy the Template ID
# 4. Go to Account → API Keys → copy your Public Key
#
# Rename this file to .env.local and fill in the values below.

VITE_EMAILJS_SERVICE_ID=service_dti24jr
VITE_EMAILJS_TEMPLATE_ID=template_r0du94b
VITE_EMAILJS_PUBLIC_KEY=ATBNdv3qjLNWi0z9t
